==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in 1788. {{suffix|abolition|ist|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈæ.bə.lɪʃ.n̩.ɪst/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈæ.bə.lɪʃ.n̩.ɪst/|/ˈæ.bə.lɪʃ.n̩.əst/|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{label|en|historical}} In favor of the abolition of slavery. {{defdate|since the late 18<sup>th</sup> century}}<ref name=SOED/>

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A person who favors the [[abolition]] of any particular institution. {{defdate|since the late 18<sup>th</sup> century}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=6}}</ref>
# {{label|en|historical|US}} A person who favored or [[advocate]]d the abolition of [[slavery]]. {{defdate|since the late 18<sup>th</sup> century}}<ref name=SOED/>

